# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
#  DrFX Quantum v5.0 — Environment Configuration
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# Server
PORT=3000

# Security — generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
JWT_SECRET=generate_with_openssl_rand_hex_32

# Admin account (auto-created on first run)
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@drfx.com
ADMIN_PASSWORD=your_secure_password

# PostgreSQL
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://drfx:password@localhost:5432/drfx_quantum
DB_USER=drfx
DB_PASS=password
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=drfx_quantum

# AI Assistant (optional) — get a key at https://openrouter.ai
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_openrouter_api_key_here

# Crypto Payments (optional) — get keys at https://nowpayments.io
NOWPAYMENTS_API_KEY=your_nowpayments_api_key_here
NOWPAYMENTS_IPN_SECRET=your_nowpayments_ipn_secret_here

# ── Ecosystem additions (Phase 1) ──────────────────────────────
# TradingView webhook shared secret — generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
# Until set, /api/webhooks/tradingview rejects every request.
TRADINGVIEW_WEBHOOK_SECRET=generate_with_openssl_rand_hex_32
# @username of the channel signals broadcast to (must exist as a 'channel' chat)
SIGNAL_CHANNEL_USERNAME=signals

# The following are used only AFTER you wire the security middleware / refresh
# tokens per INTEGRATION.md (require `npm i helmet express-rate-limit cookie-parser`).
NODE_ENV=development
# Comma-separated CORS allowlist, e.g. https://app.yourdomain.com,https://yourdomain.com
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=
# Access/refresh token lifetimes (refresh-token auth is opt-in; see INTEGRATION.md)
ACCESS_TTL=15m
REFRESH_TTL_DAYS=30
